author: cbs8
title: 2 killed in head-on collision in Calcasieu Parish
text:
LEBLEU SETTLEMENT, La. (AP) - Louisiana State Police say two people were killed in a head-on crash in Calcasieu Parish.
The collision happened Saturday morning on Louisiana Highway 397 about a mile north of Interstate Highway 10 near the community of LeBleu Settlement.
A state police news release says the preliminary investigation showed a 2004 Chevrolet pickup truck driven by 28-year-old Cortny Paul Vidalier of Rayne was traveling north on Louisiana 397 when the truck crossed into oncoming traffic. The truck hit a southbound Hyundai Genesis driven by 30-year-old Erin Michel Atlow of Lake Charles.
Both drivers were pronounced dead at the scene by the Calcasieu Parish coroner's office.
No passengers were in the vehicles.
Toxicology samples were taken and will be submitted for analysis, and the crash remains under investigation.
